					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">In the case of an mp3 player, that'd pass one threshold i think is rather significant: the sound isn't processed in any way by the NES. It's just passively mixed.  A side-point to that is it could be done with or without the internals;  and both methods require some tampering. But on the other hand, the trigging of sounds is still some level of interaction between the unit, the player module, and the user.<br /><br />(some comments on the last item were made just as i hit post)<br /><br />Edit: expansion sound synths are also just passively mixed.</div>

					
